version_description: With the capo on the 4th fret, it's much easier to play correctly with enough fret space.
Transcribed from a live performance. Not included the instrumental at the end. In the introduction and verse, there is an open 5th string played before repeating the pattern again.
The chords are mainly barre chords. The open chords are used in the bridge.

song_name: I Dont Want To Talk About It

version_description: The whole song is picked but strumming sounds good too.

Chords taken from the sheet music and placed where they occur in the lyrics. Like a lot of IG songs, there are a lot of chords and an alternate tuning. But, they form patters and DADGAD makes for easy fretting and killer sound.
I have simplified the chords for this song and made it clearer where the chord changes are.
The only other version is not transposable and has some minor chord flaws.
